* VersaLogic VersaAPI Sample Code - 20220223
*
* This code is given with no guarantees and is intended to be used as an 
* example of how to use the VersaAPI software package and to check the 
* operation post install. This code will work with various VersaLogic 
* single board computers.
*
* Default Program Description: 
* i2cAPI_sample
*      - Example of using the VersaAPI I2C API calls.
* 
* Note: By default, the VersaLogic API header file VL_OSALib.h will need to
* be copied into the local directory. 
*
* Note: i2cdev-tool will need to be installed to use VersaAPI I2C API calls.
*
* This code has been compiled and run using gcc on Ubuntu 18.04.03 LTS, 
* kernel 4.15.0-88-generic, with VersaAPI version 1.8.0.  A Linux
* compatible Makefile has been provided with this .c file for an example
* of how to compile this code.
*
* Usage: 	make clean	=> Removes executable application and all 
*				   dependant .o files.
*		make 		=> Builds 'i2cAPI_sample' application.
*
* Build fruit is an example application 'i2cAPI_sample' in the current directory.
* From the Linux command prompt, as root run: ./i2cAPI_sample -h for a list
* of command line parameters.
*

